# ─── Frontend build (Netlify) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Client-side marker (safe to expose) used to attribute outbound clicks.
VITE_TRAVELPAYOUTS_MARKER=""

# Leave this unset. Netlify proxies /api/* to Render server-to-server (see
# ../netlify.toml), so the frontend's fetch calls stay relative ("/api/...")
# and never leave Netlify's own origin from the browser's point of view —
# that's what makes the session cookie first-party instead of a
# often-blocked third-party cookie. Setting this would make requests go
# directly to Render, cross-origin, undoing that.
VITE_API_URL=""
